	(text_box "Bootstrap Cap (BOOTx - OUTx)\n\nFor STL110N10F7, since V_GS(th, max) = 4.5V and R_DS(on, max) spec'd at V_GS = 10V, VCC = 10V set in FW\n\nC_BOOT(min) >= (10*Q_g)/V_GS = (10*72nC)/10V = 72nF\n\nBut take 1uF from EVSPIN32G4 for plenty of safety buffer against voltage sag while remaining small enough to fully recharge when GLSx on"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 220.98 38.1167 0)
		(size 60.96 22.3626)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "10dc809b-c166-4dab-b09a-699ce9b6da8d")
	)
	(text_box "PGA Configuration: Inverting Mode (non-inverting disallows DC bias) (AN5306 3.4.1)\n\nVINP (OPP/non-inverting)\n- HW: NC, free up pins with OPAMPx_VINP for other periphs\n- FW: VP_SEL[1:0] = 11 to cut off VINP and route internal DAC ch (RM0440 25.3.4)\n\nVINM (OPN/inverting)\n- HW: small R to limit curr (R1_internal=10k => G_error=0.1%)\n- FW: VM_SEL[1:0] = 10 to enable PGA mode (internal feedback R's) (AN5306 3.4.1)\n\nVOUT (OPO)\n- HW: NC, free up pins with OPAMPx_VOUT for other periphs\n- FW: OPAINTOEN = 1 to cut off VOUT and route internal ADC ch (RM0440 25.3.4)\n\nPGA_GAIN[4:0] = 8 to 13 to implement an inverting amplifier (12=>-31, 13=>-63)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 195.58 109.22 0)
		(size 86.36 33.02)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "8784e90b-d30e-47a6-a916-52a31b3cc497")
	)
	(text_box "Transfer Function: V_OUT = V_DAC - ( |G_inverting| * V_SHUNT )\n- To keep 0A midpoint at VDD / 2 = 1.65V, config DAC at 2048\n- Want G=-63 for bench testing (2A) & G=-31 for regular riding (<50A)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 195.58 142.24 0)
		(size 86.36 10.16)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "a52eb0f4-67f5-4039-9986-a56bc20aa817")
	)
	(text_box "Asymmetric Gate Drive (GHSx/GLSx - GATE)\n\nTurn-off (gate pulled low) faster due to discharge thru D, so shoot-through avoided. Optional series R to damp voltage spikes in the path.\n\nTurn-on (gate pulled high) slowed by R to reduce voltage spikes\n\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 220.98 19.8393 0)
		(size 60.96 18.2607)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "d0eff5b7-bef8-48a7-ab31-f6eeb9fb9502")
	)
	(text_box "External Filtering Capacitor: DNP since unnecessary (theoretically)\n\nSTM32G431C6 datasheet gives GBW_min=7MHz & BW_PGA=GBW/G, so\nG_worst=-63 => BW_worst=7MHz/64 =109kHz > f_usual < 50kHz"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 195.58 152.4 0)
		(size 86.36 10.16)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "dd330900-9cf4-47c6-9eca-12150519a564")
	)
	(text_box "Shunt Resistor\n\nFor a +/-50mV drop at +/-50A, R = 1.0m = 2.0m || 2.0m\n\nPair of parallel resistors, so 50A cts => 2.5W total (> 1.25W each)\n\nAt +/-2A, drop is +/-2mV, but use OPAMP configured in PGA mode (and voltage bias from internal DAC connection) to map to ADC range accordingly (bench testing will use way higher gain than while riding it fr)\n\nReason for not having an external resistor network for current sensing is it would mean a fixed gain, thus it could not be flexible for both bench testing and actually rides.\n\nLayout Note: Using just regular 2-pin resistors despite the choice of symbol (4-pin kelvin sense)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 220.98 60.4793 0)
		(size 60.96 43.6606)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "e4389e69-24d6-4360-8d21-6851cb2e43b7")
	)
